<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Willis</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-24"><hi rend="italic">November 24,
                                        1893</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>The brevity and uncertainty of your telegrams are embarrassing. You
                                will insist upon amnesty and recognition of obligations of the
                                Provisional Government as essential conditions of restoration. All
                                interests will be promoted by prompt action.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q.
                                Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>